Reconnaissance, interception, and rapid response — one platform, multiple missions.
IMGMARK:1e9c09_ffc82e355e1145c9a40d023fa020125e~mv2.jpg
Autonomous Detection, Tracking & Interception
No need for personnel with drone jamming guns on-site. The T.Interceptor MP intercepts threats autonomously, while net-based capture minimizes collateral impact to the surrounding environment.
IMGMARK:1e9c09_0ec80f054543497b8d292f1740ef194d~mv2.jpg
Form Follows Function
The T. Interceptor MP breaks from the utilitarian bulk of conventional defense platforms. Its compact, muscular silhouette communicates readiness and versatility — a form shaped equally for high-speed pursuit and steady reconnaissance. Every surface is resolved with intent, projecting capability without unnecessary visual complexity.
IMGMARK:1e9c09_0e0a98e8edc3480e816d4ddfcf163ed4~mv2.jpg
Flight Testing & Validation
From controlled indoor environments to open-field scenarios, each flight test validates the system's autonomous detection, tracking, and net-based capture performance. Iterative testing under real-world conditions ensures reliability across diverse operational environments — refining flight dynamics, sensor accuracy, and structural durability before deployment.
IMGMARK:1e9c09_a081c01a186846719aff7004c9e0b183~mv2.png
IMGMARK:1e9c09_a47abfb4fa7e4398a0225033dc8fea93~mv2.png
IMGMARK:1e9c09_1ec62e81aaf14ab6ae8a56e7570fee73~mv2.png
The rear-mounted battery module is designed for rapid field replacement — minimizing downtime between missions. The tool-free extraction mechanism allows operators to swap power units in seconds, keeping the system mission-ready with minimal interruption.
IMGMARK:1e9c09_809e9c3ccaeb4e02a9b5adb644865022~mv2.png
Multi-Sensor Gimbal System
Equipped with a high-performance stabilized gimbal integrating visible light, laser rangefinder, and thermal imaging — enabling all-weather target identification, distance measurement, and tracking across day and night operations.
IMGMARK:1e9c09_d9d36d637f504a6abd48473b3c052bbb~mv2.png
Angled Net Launcher — CG-Aligned Design
The capture net launcher is mounted at a calculated angle rather than horizontal. This ensures the reaction force during net deployment passes through the drone's center of gravity, preventing destabilizing torque that could cause mid-flight rollover. The angled geometry is seamlessly integrated into the body's surface language, turning an engineering constraint into a defining design detail.
